    <description>The A to Z Rules, the Campaigns of Napoleon 1796-1815, is the fourth in a series od fast playing rules for historical miniatures. It is compatible with all basing systems and can be played on a battalion, regimental, or brigade scale. It will enable you to play a short scenario in three hours or recreate a massive day long battle in brigae scale within five to eight hours. The heart of the rules are the intiative and action allocation systems. Combined with morale variables, these are the most critical areas determinging the flow of the game. They are also areas of great flexibility and changes can be made to recreate local conditions, commander capabilities, or scenario anomalies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
